title: Smiling Mind (Free Mindfulness)
description: Evidence-informed, completely free mindfulness app for all ages, including programs for kids, teens, and adults.

title: Insight Timer (Guided Meditations)
description: Large library of free guided meditations and calming music; optional premium courses.

title: UCLA Mindful (Free Guided Meditations)
description: Free guided practices from UCLA’s Mindful Awareness Research Center (MARC).

description: Free app developed by the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs to build a simple, consistent mindfulness practice.

description: Science-based well-being training app from the Center for Healthy Minds with free core content.

description: Clear overview of autism for families from a leading children’s hospital.

description: Brief, animated explanation of autism by Neuroscientifically Challenged.

description: Educational YouTube channel by an autistic creator covering traits, masking, and everyday strategies.

description: A short ‘Three Bears’ themed explainer touching on autism spectrum understanding for kids.

description: Conversations by autistic hosts about everyday life, identity, and support.

title: Autism Stories (Autism Personal Coach)
description: Interviews spotlighting autistic adults, advocates, and professionals.

description: Strengths-based perspectives and practical support for autistic people and families.

title: 1800RESPECT – Sunny App Stories (Neurodiversity & Safety)
description: Short, accessible conversations about safety, consent, and support for diverse audiences.

description: Interviews with researchers, educators, and neurodivergent voices on thriving with ND brains.

description: Speech recognition for non-standard speech. Offers free trial and accessibility pilots; contact for supported free access.

description: Experimental app that helps people with speech impairments communicate using personalized speech recognition and text-to-speech.

title: Microsoft Live Captions (Windows)
description: On-device live captions that transcribe speech from system audio and microphone. Helpful for comprehension and communication.

title: Android Live Transcribe (Speech-to-Text)
description: Real-time speech-to-text captions powered by Google on Android devices.

title: Apple Live Captions & Type to Speak
description: System features for captioning audio and communicating by typing, available on iPhone, iPad, and Mac.

title: LetMeTalk AAC
description: Free picture-based AAC app with customizable boards available on Android and iOS.

title: CBoard (Open Source AAC)
description: Open-source AAC web app with symbol-based communication supporting multiple languages.

title: Jitsi Meet (Push-to-Talk + Captions)
description: Free, open-source video meetings with live transcription and push-to-talk, useful for remote speech practice.

title: Keeble/Keedogo (Assistive Keyboards)
description: Alternative keyboards by AssistiveWare with larger keys, configurable layouts, and auditory feedback. Free trials available.

title: Voice Access (Android hands-free)
description: Control Android by voice and dictate text hands-free, helpful for motor and speech challenges.

title: Windows Speech Recognition
description: Built-in dictation and command control on Windows, enabling speech-to-text and navigation.
